# Import packages
import numpy as np
import random
from bokeh.io import output_file, show
from bokeh.plotting import figure

# Create an array
x_array = np.array([10,20,30,40,50,60])
y_array = np.array([50,60,70,80,90,100])

# Create a line plot
plot = figure()
plot.line(x_array, y_array)

# Output plot
show(plot)
In [129]:
# Import packages
import numpy as np
import random
from bokeh.io import output_file, show
from bokeh.plotting import figure

# Create arrays
leonardo_Excercise = np.array([616, 1267, 839, 329, 1212, 675, 1241, 1250, 695, 856, 890, 1523, 1719, 750, 937, 1482])
Class_Frequency = np.array([17.85, 10.40, 13.22, 16.95, 11.19, 14.80, 9.49, 9.04, 9.94, 13.56, 10.40, 4.86, 5.65, 6.89, 7.01, 6.55])

# Create plot
plot = figure(title = "Scatter plot", x_axis_label = "leonardo_Excercise", y_axis_label ="Class_Frequency")
plot.circle(leonardo_Excercise, Class_Frequency, size = 30, alpha = 0.5)

# show plot
show(plot)

# Create arrays
leonardo_Excercise = np.array([616, 1267, 839, 329, 1212, 675, 1241, 1250, 695, 856, 890, 1523, 1719, 750, 937, 1482])
Average_Class_Rating = np.array([4.119, 4.149, 4.113, 4.127, 4.13, 4.079, 4.055, 4.116, 4.171, 4.16, 4.087, 4.143, 4.154, 4.17, 4.158, 4.104])

# Create plot
plot = figure(title = "Scatter plot", x_axis_label = "leonardo_Excercise", y_axis_label ="Average_Class_Rating")
plot.circle(leonardo_Excercise, Average_Class_Rating, size = 30, alpha = 0.5)

# show plot
show(plot)
